    <item>
      <title>14.05 The Interview</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-05-the-interview/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-05-the-interview/</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 11 Nov 2024 13:16:54 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.05 The Interview&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-04-the-late-shift/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A civilian doctor knowledgeable in smallpox. Kokuyou was the only one Maomao knew of.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A young man with half his face scarred by smallpox, and an easy-going personality that thought nothing of his unfortunate past.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That was the person Maomao sent the letter to.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-center"&gt;&amp;#8216;&lt;em&gt;Ahhh, I’m &lt;/em&gt;coming&lt;em&gt;! Yayyyy&lt;/em&gt;!&amp;#8217;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She got a really simple reply. Just as imagined.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This was the man who had a criminal record of attempting to take the court lady exam while in drag. If you invited him over from the other side, no way was he going to turn down the opportunity.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although, his reply came attached with a letter from Sazen.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sazen-san, is the person currently working at the apothecary, right?” Yo looked at the letter with a tilt of her head. It was much thicker than the letter from Kokuyou.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The two of them checked the contents. To summarise the letter that was brimming with sadness, inviting sympathy, it was: “Don’t take Kokuyou away!” There were tear-stains on the paper. You could believe it was a petition letter offered up by a wife to stop her husband from going to war.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“When did he become Doctor’s wife?” Yo asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Beats me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was unknown whether Yo was serious or joking.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Anyway, Kokuyou himself was on board with it, so he will be coming at once.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The interviewers were her dad, Luomen, Court Physician Liu, the old court physician, and one other high-ranking court physician.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The old court physician decided to take the opportunity to see Kokuyou before he went back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As his referees, Maomao and Yo were on clerk duty in the corner of the room.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou was smiling foolishly like always. His attire was slightly better than usual because he had removed the cloth that covered half his face when he sat before the interviewers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He looked more striking with the scars on his handsome face.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m Kokuyou. Pleased to meet you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I heard you’re knowledgeable in treating smallpox. How about it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Needless to say, it was Court Physician Liu who proceeded with the talks.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Exactly so. My master inoculated me with pus from a smallpox patient. I developed smallpox, it got worse, and I turned out like this. I was really lucky that I didn’t die.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As always, this man spoke of unfortunate things bluntly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Do you mean the symptoms worsened after infection control measures were implemented?” Luomen asked to confirm.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I had a younger twin brother. My master wanted to see what happens when you inoculate twins raised in the same environment with different pus. We were infected on purpose.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was human experimentation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although Maomao did such things as well, it wasn’t to the extent of Kokuyou’s master.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And the result?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My symptoms worsened and my younger brother just got a mild fever.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Where was the pus that inoculated your younger brother sourced from?”&lt;br&gt;“Where is your master now?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The court physicians’ interests shifted from the interview to the experiment Kokuyou had undergone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My master died. I’m in a fix since he didn’t leave behind his research materials.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, does your younger brother know?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My younger brother also died. When he saw my pockmarked face, he was so shocked he stabbed our master. That was the reason no materials were left behind. Afterwards, my younger brother hung himself out of remorse.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brutal…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She heard that his master died, but it was much more brutal than she imagined.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo’s face had paled. The court physicians were also put off. Only Luomen looked at Kokuyou sadly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It was over ten years ago. I’ve been studying my master’s research the entire time, but it’s quite the undertaking. Anyway, I&amp;#8217;ve brought the materials of my research relating to epidemics.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu wordlessly accepted the materials and looked through them. He also showed it to Luomen and shared it with the other court physicians.&amp;nbsp; Despite his flippant way of speaking, his materials seemed legit–in particular, the old court physician nodded many times.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I’m curious…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought about having Kokuyou show them to her later as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She suddenly looked at Yo, who was hanging her head with a pale face. Maomao shook the other court lady’s shoulders. “Our clerk duty isn’t done yet.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“R-right.” Yo flusteredly moved her brush.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is this ‘lifetime immunisation’?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It is a phrase my master used occasionally. It means not contracting the disease for the rest of your life after contracting it once. I suppose I used a phrase translated from the language of my master’s country.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can you assert this to be true?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I cannot, but I have inoculated myself with pus every three years and haven’t developed the disease. Also, I have not heard of anyone contracting the disease again after contracting it once at the smallpox village despite several outbreaks. I believe if you increase the parameters, exceptions would also increase, but to my knowledge, it is generally the case that after getting it once, you won’t get it again.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems the views of the four court physicians aligned.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Would it be alright if we copy your materials?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou didn’t reply, all smiles.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We’ll pay you fifty silvers.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sure,” Kokuyou said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Surprisingly, this man had good money sense.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also, in terms of employment, it will not be at the imperial court. You will be going to the countryside. Would it be alright even if the stay becomes long-term?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou was all smiles again.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We’ll pay you two silvers per day.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou did not move.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;How about two silvers and a half, no, three silvers?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Still no movement.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Fine&lt;/em&gt;. Five silvers!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was extremely generous.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou finally nodded.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I-is that okay? I think five silver is on par with the treatment of a high-ranking court physician, though.” Yo, becoming concerned, shook Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“With you being an irreplaceable talent, we will give you this much. If this was a commodity, it could rise ten times, a hundred times in value.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;But with Court Physician Liu as the other party, they won’t be bullish,&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, five silvers.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Is he trying to raise it even higher?&lt;/em&gt; she thought.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou lifted three fingers. “No need for five silvers. I’ll be happy with three. Also, can you prepare a carriage to get me there and provide me with sleeping quarters and food separately?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, we’ll prepare that for you as much as you like.” The court physicians stroke down their chests in relief.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After the interview was over, Maomao and Yo were entrusted to guide Kokuyou. It was to hand him his court physician robes and the bare minimum of tools before he went to his work posting.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Fufufu, it’s good fortune that I was able to get a government job. We’ll be together, Yo,” Kokuyou said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m also happy that I will be with Doctor, but it’s not a fun workplace.” Yo’s face paled.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How is it at the posting now?” Maomao wanted to ask in detail.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We get around one to two patients per day as of now. But the village itself has been locked down, so the mood is bad. The frustration grows by the day,&amp;#8221; Yo replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yo hasn’t personally examined a patient yet, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I’ve been told that I will be going as Court Physician Lao’s assistant.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That’s right. The old court physician was Court Physician Lao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even Maomao remembered the name of the boss of her posting. More than anything, she remembered names that were easy to remember like Wanwan-senpai, but she just ended up calling Court Physician Lao the old court physician, taking the name Lao (老) for the meaning of old.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Once the number of workers is secured, I might be entering the village as well,&amp;#8221; Yo said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;If you don’t want to, you don’t have to do it,” Maomao said honestly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I believe it is possible because it is me. The things that I can do that Maomao-san can’t are limited, after all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then it’s fine.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The court lady wasn’t scared of just the epidemic. The frustration of the oppressed residents would fall onto the court physicians on site.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My dad told me he will be coming with me. He’s eager since the pay is good too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo’s family had taken care of the surviving children of their village and moved to the capital. It might represent a golden opportunity to earn food expenses.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Come to think of it, Kokuyou, are you good with three silvers as your pay?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yup. It’s much higher than the sum I get for showing my face at the apothecary in the pleasure district,” Kokuyou said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sorry &lt;em&gt;for the low pay.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao gave him a stiff smile.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sazen will probably manage.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sazen just had low self-esteem. He wasn’t bad as a herbalist. However, he had a part of him that didn’t forgive failure. Since the effectiveness of medicine was determined by individual differences, there was no need to brood over it. Just that he will have to manage when it came to recognising the time to quit when the medicine wasn’t a good fit.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But five silvers, huuuh? Court Physician Liu, was it? He’s a good doctor,” Kokuyou said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He’s an outstanding doctor. Just strict,&amp;#8221; Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu was on par with Luomen, a noted doctor of Li.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He may be strict, but I’m happy that he seriously appreciated me. Among them some worked me hard for an entire day for a few coppers. He even gave me fifty silvers to copy my materials. I’ll have to do a good job. I need to treat the people who appreciate me right.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, what about people who didn’t appreciate you?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ll treat them in the way they deserve.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was oddly deep, so Maomao decided to not ask any more deeply. “I don’t think you were worked that hard, though.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ll demand a wage increase to five silvers when the time comes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s only if you succeed in getting that increase.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That might be difficult.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In other words, he will be getting busy.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The materials just now, can you show it to me too?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The materials were also approved by high-ranking court physicians. It possessed that much value.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sure, but can you pay me fifty silvers?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ugh.” That was two to three months of Maomao’s salary. “Can’t you give me a friend’s discount?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Let me think about it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;His haggling is actually on par with Rahan&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-06-dining-hall/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-05-the-interview/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5011-68e0e56eddf94' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20251004#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5011&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5011-68e0e56eddf94' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5011-68e0e56eddf94' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-05-the-interview/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
