    <item>
      <title>15.03 Peach Blossom Bookstore</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-03-peach-blossom-bookstore/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-03-peach-blossom-bookstore/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Sep 2025 14:58:02 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;15.03 Peach Blossom&amp;nbsp;Bookstore&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: The peach blossom symbolises a lot of things, but the key one for this chapter would probably be &lt;em&gt;romance&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#8230;&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-02-the-story-of-the-villainess/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The next day, Maomao went to work as always.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The book by Chou San had already passed through the hands of all the courtesans at Verdigris Mansion, so there were no issues with Maomao taking it home.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Daylight hours had gotten shorter as well, so she thought to read it in between work.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh? You brought in something unusual.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Li showed interest. Her senior, who used to be earnest and square in personality, had become square in the broadness of his shoulders recently. He had been eating nothing but chicken lately, saying that it was good for growing muscle, and had been giving Maomao the skin.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pairin-neechan would be delighted if I were to introduce him to her.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But she shouldn&amp;#8217;t. It would be troubling if it created an awkward atmosphere with Rihaku.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you want to, you can read it. I’m not free yet.” Maomao was wrapping the medicine into paper pouches.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I’ve… read this before,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How surprising. You read these sorts of things, too?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The story was springing up everywhere like bamboo shoots after the Shi clan insurrection. Books have been spreading more even before then, which led to it being read in turn at the medical office too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Was this the result of Jinshi popularising novels?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“In the early days, there were a lot of books with questionable content on the market, but I recall that before long the dodgy ones disappeared. I remember reading that book once the popularity died down.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“When was that?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Before we went to the western capital. I don’t think it’s been two years.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao checked the calendar in her mind. Was it around a year and a half after the Shi clan insurrection?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you want to read this kind of story, I’ll introduce you to a bookstore that has a lot of these. I know the owner. She’s fond of gossip.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh? Court Physician Li goes to that kind of shop, I see.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“N-no, I-I was just accompanying!” Court Physician Li frantically clarified. She could see his clenched fists were muscular with prominent blue veins.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Do you have any idea about what kind of person the author could be?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why are you asking me? Hmmm, based on the surprisingly beautiful style of writing, they must have been educated.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Anything else?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Anything else, you ask me…” Court Physician Li groaned with the book in one hand. “Occasionally, failed government officials and those folks who have given up on the imperial examination would try their hand at popular things for the sake of money. You know how they write beautifully, but there&amp;#8217;s this characteristic vibe&amp;#8211;get what I mean?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I get it too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A vibe a bit like they&amp;#8217;re looking down on you.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;“But this book is different from those.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Seems like he couldn’t explain it well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had a sense that Court Physician Li wasn’t good at putting things into words.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Anyway, can you tell me about that gossip-loving shop?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So, you want to go there after all?” Court Physician Li took a sheet of paper for record-keeping use and smoothly wrote on it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He wrote ‘Peach Blossom Bookstore.’ It seems to be located at the western end of the capital.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Peach blossom…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Li panicked as if he had noticed Maomao’s fixed gaze. “It’s not that kind of shop!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, I know. Thank you.” Maomao bowed her head and slipped the paper into her bosom pocket.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When work ended, she immediately headed for the bookstore she was referred to.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Excuse me. To the capital’s west gate.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She had hailed a carriage in this rare instance to save time on both getting there and coming back. Normally, Maomao was a little stingy, but the sun set early in winter. She thought it would be better in case it got too late and there wouldn&amp;#8217;t be any carriages left.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Peach Blossom Bookstore was situated on the first side street coming off the main street from the west gate. It helped that the driver knew the bookstore. It seems that occasionally people with curious tastes would buy a large volume of books then go home, so the driver has made the round trip before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, I’ll entrust you to bring me back as well,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Be back before the next bell rings,” the driver said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao entered the bookstore. It was dim inside and had the characteristic smell of paper. The overflowing bookshelves were crammed with books, and books that couldn’t fit on the shelves were left on the floor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Excuse me.” Maomao headed deeper inside. “Excuuuse me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is it?”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She heard a sleepy voice.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A portly woman emerged sluggishly from within. Was she well into her thirties? She had a plate in hand, which had a pair of chopsticks stabbed into a daikon.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahh, I forgot to close up shop.” The woman bit into the stabbed daikon. Her cheeks, which looked like swollen rice cakes, were excessively glossy.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you’re here to buy, do it quickly. I want to eat my dinner,” she said and went to put the closed signboard outside. It seems she would only wait for Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I do want to shop, but…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Excuse me, but do you know this book?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“This book?” the woman looked at the book Maomao brought over. “Ahh.” She clapped her hands together, then started to rummage through the mountain of books on the floor. “Is this it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The book the woman showed Maomao was the same as the one she brought in. The title and name of the author were both the same. Although the text inside was also the same, it didn&amp;#8217;t have the same writer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If the manuscript was handwritten, then either one could be the copied version. Otherwise, both could be copied versions.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hehehe. This book is quite interesting. Yeah, I’m aware it’s a classic. You&amp;#8217;d already know how it ends if you know the story of our Moon Prince.” The woman continued while eating the rest of the daikon, “I liked how strangely vivid the minor details were. But, well, it’s behind the times and similar stories sell for dirt cheap nowadays.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The woman tapped the books that couldn’t fit on the shelves. They were all works with similar titles.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Do you know the author of this book?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Nope. At the very least, there is no author by the name of Chou San.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Really?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The woman circled the suspecting Maomao. She was light on her feet despite her large build. “Yeah. At the very least, there is no work by that author among the books in this shop. Failed poets who can’t make ends meet might publish under a changed name, but it doesn’t seem like this would be the case.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The woman was neither young nor a beauty. However, Maomao knew that she held absolute power in this shop. In a sense, the bookstore was the castle she was the lord of.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ah, but…” the woman clapped her hands together, then flipped through the book. “This expression is peculiar to the north, so there&amp;#8217;s a good chance that they hail from Shihoku Province. They&amp;#8217;re probably fairly well-educated.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao’s eyes widened, and she gulped. “Could it be the writing of an upper-class woman?” &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What am I thinking? &lt;/em&gt;she thought to herself.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Nah, probably not. I couldn’t see signs of that.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“…” Maomao was dejected by the clear answer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Did you think it was written by someone you know?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even if it’s not someone you know, do you want to know the author?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Do you know?” Maomao leaned over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even if I don’t know the author, the guy who produced the copy might know. Looking up handwriting is child’s play for me. Also, if the same book comes up for sale again, I&amp;#8217;ll ask where they got it from. Should I hold onto it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please do. As thanks&amp;#8230; I’ll give you what I can.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even Maomao had saved up a reasonable amount of money.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Alrighty. You can leave it to this Xiongmao-neechan.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Xiongmao?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What about it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I just found your name very familiar,” Maomao said to the woman who was literally like a panda.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So, what’s your name?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s Maomao.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Your name is also very familiar to me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That&amp;#8217;s just how it was.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N: random, but I can&amp;#8217;t help noticing that some people are calling this arc &amp;#8220;WN17&amp;#8221; &amp;#8230;.how did you guys get two arcs ahead of me? &lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;Anyway, new name:&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;sup&gt;熊猫 &amp;#8211; Shonmao &amp;#8211; Panda&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;sup&gt;(literally Bear Cat, hence the parallel with Maomao&amp;#8217;s name) &lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;After this, Silksong calls, so see you all in a few week&amp;#8217;s time maybe?&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(Next Chapter)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-03-peach-blossom-bookstore/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5556-68e0e56eec706' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20251004#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5556&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5556-68e0e56eec706' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5556-68e0e56eec706' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/15-03-peach-blossom-bookstore/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
