    <item>
      <title>14.18 Random Attacker</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-18-random-attacker/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-18-random-attacker/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 12 Jan 2025 04:34:44 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.18 Random Attacker&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;T/N: Not sure if relevant, but the title of the chapter could also mean someone who brings misfortune with them wherever they go.&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-17-changsha-peerless/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo was put into the same section as Maomao when she returned. The section was relatively busy with a lot of military officers, but it seems Yo, who had experienced a site that was more intense, found it rather quiet. Considering how Court Physician Lao must have anticipated that and had her come back to this section, let’s say it was as expected of the wisdom of his age.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And since Yao, En’en, and Changsha worked in close vicinity, it looks like they would be continuing with the girls’ talk from hell for now. Yao looked tired when she left the dorm but at the same time she had a bashful expression. As it went on for the entire day, En’en was gaunt as if she lost half her weight.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;From the looks of it, they must have spoken favourably of Rahan.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What’s so good about him?&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought from the bottom of her heart, while thinking to let it go.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Changsha is clear-cut about her preferences, so it&amp;#8217;s a good thing they get along relatively well,&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought. Depending on the situation, her personality could produce an irreparable rift.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Truly a relief&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought deeply. Considering that poison can occasionally become medicine, it looks like Changsha suited as a wonder drug for Yao and En’en.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;All things considered, she couldn’t help thinking that all of the court physician assistants have strong personalities. Naturally, their gathering wasn’t by chance–they had to be whimsical enough to consider becoming an assistant to first take the exam, and the weaker individuals would then be picked off by Yao and the court physicians, so it was obvious that the only ones left were the bold ones.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So, would it be mean to say it was amusing in a sense that En’en had been placed in a tight spot?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-san, is it okay to write the log like this?” Yo asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I think it’s fine,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As the sections had different bosses, the way things were done differed slightly. Yo, having taken that into account as well, asked Maomao about every little thing. It was a pain, but it was the correct way for the first time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Then, as there was a young maiden around, the military officers approached with wide grins. Maomao threatened them off by clacking her teeth. It goes without saying that the beefy Court Physician Ri and Wanwan-senpai also spoke to them, so there were no holes in the protection of Yo from strange insects.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Nonetheless, there was a fool who did approach her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hey, hey, how was it at the smallpox site?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Approaching without reading the room was the one who currently had his pay docked, Tianyu. He slipped past his natural enemy Court Physician Ri’s fists and deliberately came over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Were the dead autopsied?” he asked.&lt;br&gt;“The swelling isn’t just on the surface of their skin but on the inside as well?”&lt;br&gt;“They don’t burst?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He prioritised his curiosity to talk to Yo, so Maomao surreptitiously called Court Physician Ri over to have him fiercely land a fist on him for her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You don’t need to answer him,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If you were to carelessly dissect a smallpox body, the infection would be scary. Even if one were to have caught smallpox before, there was no asserting that they wouldn’t catch it again.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.” Yo was strong. She had worked in the inner palace for two years after all. She could probably get on with her work without paying any mind to Tianyu at least. “Actually, we autopsied a lot of them.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Is that so?” Maomao was surprised at the unexpected answer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The body of the first child…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How did it go?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo shook her head. “There wasn’t anything unusual about it. I am not in the position to pursue it deeply either.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The court physician who carried out the autopsy had probably done it because there was a point of concern. He must have been bothered about how they got infected.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Where did the infection come from?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao continued to work while she was left feeling disturbed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The disturbing doubt was dispelled surprisingly quickly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When work ended, Court Physician Liu summoned Maomao. He had summoned her with a mysterious look, so she found herself on guard.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Could I have done something wrong?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a summoning timed to when Yo returned home.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I want to ask you again. Can we trust the man called Kokuyou or not?” Court Physician Liu asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Court Physician Liu should also be aware that his medical knowledge is impeccable,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, that I know. However, I have some concerns.” Court Physician Liu looked grim. “From what I’ve been told, Yo is close to Kokuyou.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In short, it was probably about something that couldn’t be mentioned to Yo he wanted to check with Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What did Kokuyou do?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Have you heard about first person infected in the smallpox village?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That it was a child and that the source of the infection is still unclear. Yo told me a short while ago that nothing was found in the autopsy.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;From the looks of it, it seems likely that there were facts that had been kept from Yo.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There is one thing we know from the autopsy. The child had a cut from a bladed weapon. We couldn’t get the details as the child and his family have already died, but according to the villagers, he had been attacked by a random attacker when he went on his trip. From what I’ve been told, there were similar incidents and many children had been attacked. However, the culprit has never be found.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A random attacker? By trip, do you mean…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah. When he went to another town. And although I said he had been slashed at, his injury was only a light graze on the surface of his skin.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao understood what Court Physician Liu wanted to say.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If there is something you noticed, tell me. Because of Luomen’s teachings, you don’t readily offer your thoughts, right? Try voicing to me your trivial speculation now.” Court Physician Liu urged Maomao to speak.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The goal of the random attacker is to inoculate smallpox pus on children. I don’t know if it was an experiment or a treatment to prevent children from catching smallpox. However, Yo had been purposely infected with smallpox by Kokuyou, and as a result she obtained a constitution resistant to smallpox. Court Physician Liu, are you suggesting that this smallpox epidemic was caused by Kokuyou?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I am not certain, but there is a possibility. Randomly going after children to infect them has finally resulted in one person catching smallpox. It aggravated and infected other people, turning into the current state of affairs. Any inconsistencies?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was exactly that. However, even Maomao had reservations about it “Where did the random attacker appear?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can you read a map?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu took out a map. He had gone out of his way to double check with her as a lot of people have never seen a map before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu ran his index finger from the capital to the north west. “There. It’s a three day’s walk from here.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao guessed that it was thirty &lt;em&gt;li&lt;/em&gt; in terms of distance and checked the name of the town in question that had been drawn on the map. “The man Kokuyou is contracted to come to the pleasure district apothecary a few days a month. He would be in this village here normally. An elderly man lives there. We can confirm with him.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The village Kokuyou stayed at was where Maomao would go to purchase the medicinal herbs she couldn’t cultivate herself. It wasn’t far from the capital, so it would probably take around three days to walk to the place the random attacker appeared as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’re thinking that Kokuyou can be excluded as a suspect.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. I believe the possibility is remarkably low.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Your basis being?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Theoretically, it is not impossible, but I cannot see a reason why he would purposely pick a place a three days walk away. If it were an experiment, I can see why he would want to do it at some distant town since he would have some qualms about it, but at the same time, he would have to check its development. While taking a fast horse could shorten the travel time, Kokuyou does not have the money to spare for a fast horse.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu listened to Maomao quietly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also, if he were treating children so they wouldn’t catch smallpox, he would be fine with doing it somewhere much closer. Above all, &lt;em&gt;he &lt;/em&gt;is aware of its dangers, more so than anyone else, so I doubt he would do it in a place he cannot keep his eye on.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu rubbed his chin, in thought. “I have a general idea now. Then, how about we change the intent?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The intent?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What if it wasn’t an experiment, nor was it for treatment, but it was done out of malicious intent?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Malicious intent.” The words put Maomao at a loss.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The malice of humans was fearsome. Why? People would bring harm to another despite understanding the loss they would bear. It all boiled down to self-interest.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The malicious intent rooted within the inner palace had once brought about a rebellion. Consequently, a single clan paid the price and was purged.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Do you know if Kokuyou is malicious or not?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I do not. However, I currently see him as someone who treats people equally.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou may be stingy in his dealings with Maomao, but he wouldn&amp;#8217;t make extremely unreasonable demands. Maomao’s assessment was that he wasn’t a relatively bad person considering that many look down on her for her small stature and for being female.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That being said, Maomao couldn’t assert that she was being objective.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Isn’t Court Physician Liu strict on that point because of his past experience travelling in the west with Luomen?&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Predicting everything rationally rather than acting on emotions strangely was what made a superior reliable.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Don’t think subjectively. Get an objective perspective.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And Yo would be more subjective than Maomao. That was probably why Court Physician Liu had avoided Yo and summoned Maomao. Hiding the truth of the autopsy must also be because of this.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Better I do not talk to Yo about this, right?” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That needn’t be said,” he replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I was confirming just in case.” Although Maomao was relieved that she didn’t get scolded, she had a feeling like there was something clogged in the back of her mind.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“One more thing.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;What is it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Could I have actually done something that angered him?&lt;/em&gt; Maomao jolted. She was really, really sure that she hadn’t done anything wrong…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Liu had an extremely stern look on his face. “I want you to give the Moon Prince regular health checks.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;Would it be fine to have me go?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There were plenty other court physicians that were outstanding. The likes of Maomao wasn’t even one.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s not a medical examination.” Nonetheless, Court Physician Liu looked dissatisfied. Maomao could tell that it wasn’t his will, but some other pressure that had tried to dispatch Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although Chue’s face instantly came to mind, the woman didn’t have that much power herself. The one who gave the order was likely a person considerably high-ranking, one of the few people who numbered less than the five fingers on her hand–all Chue could do was be their mouthpiece.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Certainly.” Maomao bowed her head at Court Physician Liu.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-19-health-check/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-18-random-attacker/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5249-68e0e56f1572d' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20251004#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5249&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5249-68e0e56f1572d' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5249-68e0e56f1572d' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-18-random-attacker/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
